{"ClientSettings":{"Pn":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"P"},"Sc":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"H"},"Qz":{"Cn":1,"St":0,"Qs":0,"Prod":"T"},"Ap":true,"Mute":true,"Lad":"2026-03-05T00:00:00Z","Iotd":0,"Gwb":0,"Tns":0,"Dft":null,"Mvs":0,"Flt":0,"Imp":1,"Tobn":0},"MediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As evening settles over the town of Göreme in the heart of the Cappadocia region of Türkiye, dusk reveals a landscape forged by nature and centuries of human presence. This scene is part of Göreme National Park and the Rock Sites of Cappadocia, a UNESCO World Heritage Site inscribed in 1985 for its exceptional combination of early cultural history and geological formations. These formations, often called 'fairy chimneys' or hoodoos, began as layers of volcanic ash that hardened into soft stone following eruptions of ancient Anatolian volcanoes. Over time, wind and water carved the pillars, ridges and valleys that define the region today.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.GoremeTwilight_EN-CA8343514373_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.GoremeTwilight_EN-CA8343514373_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Ancient rocks, modern lights","Title":"Evening over Göreme, Cappadocia, Türkiye","Copyright":"© ONNAJA/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.64296,34.828777/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.64296,34.828777;S9;Göreme, Cappadocia, Türkiye&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260305_GoremeTwilight\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=G%c3%b6reme+T%c3%bcrkiye&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260305_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260305_GoremeTwilight"},"Ssd":"20260305","Name":"GoremeTwilight","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"8343514373","FullDateString":"Mar. 5, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"As winter's grip on the Rila Mountains of southwestern Bulgaria begins to loosen, crocuses push through the thinning snow, signalling the arrival of spring in the country's highest mountain range. These early bloomers use stored nutrients to quickly grow in cold conditions, completing much of their life cycle before taller plants emerge. Their clustered blossoms unfurl over alpine meadows in sweeping purple ribbons, creating a striking contrast with bright snowfields and crisp morning light.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.RilaCrocuses_EN-CA7286747393_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.RilaCrocuses_EN-CA7286747393_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Crocuses in the spotlight","Title":"Purple crocus flowers, Seven Rila Lakes, Bulgaria","Copyright":"© Maya Karkalicheva/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/42.204161,23.312577/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=42.204161,23.312577;S9;Seven Rila Lakes, Bulgaria&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260304_RilaCrocuses\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Seven+Rila+Lakes+Bulgaria&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260304_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260304_RilaCrocuses"},"Ssd":"20260304","Name":"RilaCrocuses","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7286747393","FullDateString":"Mar. 4, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Today is World Wildlife Day, a United Nations observance that invites us to reflect on our well-being's deep connection to the natural world. This year's theme focuses on medicinal and aromatic plants (MAPs)—species used in traditional healing, modern medicine, cosmetics and food. The UN estimates that between 50,000 and 70,000 MAP species are harvested globally, with 70-95% of people in many developing countries relying on them for primary health care. However, many of these plants face mounting threats from habitat loss, overharvesting and illegal trade, making sustainable use essential for their future.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BabyElephant_EN-CA7349678191_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BabyElephant_EN-CA7349678191_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Guardians of the wild","Title":"African elephant calf playing with its mother, Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya","Copyright":"© Denis-Huot/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/-1.529493,35.170876/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=-1.529493,35.170876;S9;Masai Mara National Reserve, Kenya&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260303_BabyElephant\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=World+Wildlife+Day+2026&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260303_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260303_BabyElephant"},"Ssd":"20260303","Name":"BabyElephant","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7349678191","FullDateString":"Mar. 3, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Do not be fooled by how simple Ko Samui's longtail boats look from a distance; decades of local ingenuity have shaped their slender frames. These vessels, known in Thailand as 'ruea hang yao,' emerged in the early 20th century, when fishermen repurposed vehicle engines to navigate shallow waters that larger boats couldn't reach. Handcrafted plank by plank, each boat reflects generations of skill. Their hulls burst with bold, striking colours, while decorative cloth and flowers often crown the bows—Buddhist blessings meant to safeguard both the boat and its crew.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SamuiThailand_EN-CA7437752481_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SamuiThailand_EN-CA7437752481_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Floating legacies","Title":"Harbour and longtail boats at Ko Samui, Thailand","Copyright":"© Foto2rich/Shutterstock","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/9.48921,99.991724/5?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=9.48921,99.991724;S9;Ko Samui, Surat Thani, Thailand&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260302_SamuiThailand\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Ko+Samui+Thailand&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260302_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260302_SamuiThailand"},"Ssd":"20260302","Name":"SamuiThailand","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7437752481","FullDateString":"Mar. 2, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Owls are full of contradictions. Silent wings, loud opinions. They are night hunters that somehow feel ancient. From myths to cartoons, they have always had a presence. Athena's owl symbolised wisdom, while pop culture gave us lines we still quote—remember Owl from 'Winnie-the-Pooh' always sounding sure of himself?","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OwlonGuard_EN-CA7496212614_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OwlonGuard_EN-CA7496212614_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Feather you like it or not","Title":"Snowy owl near the Canadian Rockies","Copyright":"© www.harshadventure.com/Moment/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"While they are often surprisingly light, the snowy is the heaviest owl in North America.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260301_OwlonGuard\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Snowy+owl&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260301_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260301_OwlonGuard"},"Ssd":"20260301","Name":"OwlonGuard","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7496212614","FullDateString":"Mar. 1, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Moloka'i, often called the most Hawaiian of the islands, offers a slower rhythm shaped by nature and strong community ties. Formed by volcanic activity more than a million years ago, the island covers about 673 square kilometres and rises from the Pacific Ocean in long ridges and broad valleys. Unlike its busier neighbours, Moloka'i has resisted large-scale development, preserving a strong sense of local cohesion where families, traditions and stewardship of the land encapsulate central values. Life here focuses on the ocean, the land and stories passed down through generations.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.OloupenaFalls_EN-CA7570794029_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.OloupenaFalls_EN-CA7570794029_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Overflowing with community","Title":"Olo'upena Falls, island of Moloka'i, Hawaii, United States","Copyright":"© Andrew Aylett/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/21.16472,-156.8595/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=21.16472,-156.8595;S9;Olo'upena Falls, Moloka'i, Hawaii, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260228_OloupenaFalls\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Molokai&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260228_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260228_OloupenaFalls"},"Ssd":"20260228","Name":"OloupenaFalls","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7570794029","FullDateString":"Feb. 28, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"International Polar Bear Day underscores how closely these Arctic giants are tied to their frozen realms. Celebrated on February 27, the day shines a light on polar bears and the rapidly changing world beneath their paws. The world's largest land carnivores roam across vast icy landscapes, sometimes covering hundreds of kilometres in search of food. They're perfectly adapted to life on sea ice, with large paws that help them swim for kilometres.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.ArcitcCub_EN-CA9950201389_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.ArcitcCub_EN-CA9950201389_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Life on thinning ice","Title":"Polar bear cub walking across pack ice, Arctic National Wildlife Refuge, Alaska, United States","Copyright":"© Steven Kazlowski/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/68.75,-143.5/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=68.75,-143.5;S9;Arctic National Wildlife Refuge, Alaska, United States&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260227_ArcitcCub\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=International+Polar+Bear+Day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260227_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260227_ArcitcCub"},"Ssd":"20260227","Name":"ArcitcCub","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"9950201389","FullDateString":"Feb. 27, 2026"}],"PreloadMediaContents":[{"ImageContent":{"Description":"High in Ecuador's cloud forests, a young sunbittern spreads its wings in an early display, casting flashes of orange, black and white through the filtered green light. The sudden contrast cuts through the moss‑covered branches and leaf‑shadowed understorey, offering a snapshot of the species' dramatic wing patterns. Adult sunbitterns most often show these bold markings during defensive displays, briefly transforming an elusive bird into a striking spectacle.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SunbitternEcuador_EN-CA6009774194_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SunbitternEcuador_EN-CA6009774194_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Wings in rehearsal","Title":"Juvenile sunbittern displaying at nest, Ecuador","Copyright":"© Andy Rouse/naturepl.com","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"The sunbittern's wings feature eye‑like patterns, often revealed during wing displays in low forest light.","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260312_SunbitternEcuador\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Sunbittern+bird&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260312_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260312_SunbitternEcuador"},"Ssd":"20260312","Name":"SunbitternEcuador","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6009774194","FullDateString":"Mar. 12, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Spring hits differently in Cieza. It doesn't gently unfold—it erupts with colour. Between February and March, this small city in Spain's Murcia region is the epicentre of 'La Floración,' the flowering of peach trees. In a matter of days, more than 4,856 hectares—Spain's largest municipal peach production—transform into the sea of colour we see in today's image.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.PeachBloom_EN-CA5288839040_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.PeachBloom_EN-CA5288839040_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A peachy keen spring","Title":"Peach trees in bloom, Cieza, Murcia, Spain","Copyright":"© Juan Maria Coy Vergara/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/38.239372,-1.418669/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=38.239372,-1.418669;S9;Cieza, Murcia, Spain&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260311_PeachBloom\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Cieza+Spain&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260311_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260311_PeachBloom"},"Ssd":"20260311","Name":"PeachBloom","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"5288839040","FullDateString":"Mar. 11, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Have you ever wondered what happens when fire, ice and time negotiate the same territory? Iceland's Hveravellir geothermal field has the answer. In this highland hotspot, energy from the Earth's interior meets the icy surface, triggering a volatile dialogue between pressure, temperature and stone. Fumaroles hiss, steam curls into the air and the ground paints itself with sulphur whites, rust reds and ochre yellows—not only artistry, but chemical reactions driven by extreme heat. In today's image, Bláhver, a natural hot spring, dazzles in electric blue. Its colour comes from mineral- and silica-rich waters that reflect light on the surface.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.SpringIceland_EN-CA4746064568_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.SpringIceland_EN-CA4746064568_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Fire under frost","Title":"Geothermal blue pool Bláhver at Hveravellir, Iceland","Copyright":"© Juan Maria Coy Vergara/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/64.865398,-19.559103/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=64.865398,-19.559103;S9;Hveravellir, Iceland&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260310_SpringIceland\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Blahver+pool+Iceland&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260310_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260310_SpringIceland"},"Ssd":"20260310","Name":"SpringIceland","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"4746064568","FullDateString":"Mar. 10, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"National Napping Day couldn't be better timed. It falls on the Monday after Daylight Saving Time begins, when clocks move forward and we all lose an hour of sleep. Consider today an official excuse to slow down and make up for it. The sleeping grey seal in this image, spotted along Scotland's coast, is a fitting reminder for the day: rest matters.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.NappingSeal_EN-CA7649170923_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.NappingSeal_EN-CA7649170923_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A perfectly timed nap","Title":"Grey seal sleeping on the beach, Orkney Islands, Scotland","Copyright":"© Andrew Mason/Minden Pictures","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/59,-3/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=59,-3;S9;Orkney Islands, Scotland&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260309_NappingSeal\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Napping+day&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260309_0400\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260309_NappingSeal"},"Ssd":"20260309","Name":"NappingSeal","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"7649170923","FullDateString":"Mar. 9, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Every March, Daylight Saving Time begins across most of Canada, shifting clocks forward by one hour to extend evening daylight. The seasonal change has historically been linked to making better use of natural light and reducing energy use during longer spring and summer days. The idea can be traced back to 1784, when Benjamin Franklin humorously suggested earlier rising to conserve candle use. Most provinces and territories follow the shift, though Saskatchewan and a few communities in British Columbia and Nunavut remain on standard time throughout the year. The time change is known for disrupting sleep patterns, which is why the Monday after the clock change is informally known as Napping Day.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.UlmClock_EN-CA0107157724_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.UlmClock_EN-CA0107157724_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"The art of saving daylight","Title":"Astronomical clock at Town Hall of the City of Ulm, Germany","Copyright":"© Tomekbudujedomek/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/48.397026,9.993355/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=48.397026,9.993355;S9;Town Hall of the City of Ulm, Germany&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260308_UlmClock\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Daylight+Saving+Time&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260308_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260308_UlmClock"},"Ssd":"20260308","Name":"UlmClock","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"0107157724","FullDateString":"Mar. 8, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Imagine reaching the Brocken in Harz National Park, Germany, as clouds slide across the ridge. With the sun behind you, mist ahead—then a giant, haloed shadow forms. Ever wondered why climbers once feared this sight? The phenomenon, called the Brocken spectre, is an eerie natural optical effect that occurs when sunlight projects a person's shadow onto cloud or fog. Rising about 1,141 metres, the Brocken is the highest peak in northern Germany and has long inspired folklore, including tales of witches gathering here during Walpurgis Night.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.BrockenSunrise_EN-CA3220764261_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.BrockenSunrise_EN-CA3220764261_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"A legendary sunrise","Title":"Sunrise on the Brocken, Harz National Park, Germany","Copyright":"© imageBROKER/AVTG/Getty Images","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/51.799072,10.61556/4?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=51.799072,10.61556;S9;The Brocken, Harz National Park, Germany&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260307_BrockenSunrise\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=Harz+National+Park&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260307_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260307_BrockenSunrise"},"Ssd":"20260307","Name":"BrockenSunrise","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"3220764261","FullDateString":"Mar. 7, 2026"},{"ImageContent":{"Description":"Architecture blends art and technology, expressed through the built form. While many designs focus primarily on function, some buildings give equal weight to visual impact. A strong example is The Wave building complex in Vejle, Denmark, where sculptural design and practical housing come together seamlessly.","Image":{"Url":"/th?id=OHR.WaveDenmark_EN-CA6114936639_1920x1080.webp","Wallpaper":"/th?id=OHR.WaveDenmark_EN-CA6114936639_1920x1200.jpg&rf=LaDigue_1920x1200.jpg","Downloadable":true},"Headline":"Waves cast in concrete","Title":"The Wave residential building, Vejle, Denmark","Copyright":"© Frank Bach/Alamy","SocialGood":null,"MapLink":{"Url":"//platform.bing.com/geo/REST/v1/Imagery/Map/RoadVibrant/55.709099,9.5561/3?key=AsSOKo7OOz5VAtfAj0rjgaXlhCrCZI6PGbLj7GCH8IW2HUalyg4BVhqA0z77PRCj&c=en-CA&od=2&shading=flat&pp=55.709099,9.5561;S9;The Wave, Vejle, Denmark&st=pp|v:false;lv:false_trs|v:false;lv:false&ml=Basemap,Landmarks&logo=no&mapSize=386,434&da=ro","Link":""},"QuickFact":{"MainText":"","LinkUrl":"","LinkText":""},"TriviaUrl":"/search?q=Bing+homepage+quiz&filters=WQOskey:\"HPQuiz_20260306_WaveDenmark\"&FORM=HPQUIZ","BackstageUrl":"/search?q=The+Wave+building+Vejle+Denmark&form=hpcapt&filters=HpDate:\"20260306_0500\"+mgzv3configlist:\"BingQA_Encyclopedia_Layout\"","TriviaId":"HPQuiz_20260306_WaveDenmark"},"Ssd":"20260306","Name":"WaveDenmark","Market":"EN-CA","Hash":"6114936639","FullDateString":"Mar. 6, 2026"}],"LocStrings":{"LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD":"Image of the day","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_IOTD_LEARN_MORE":"Learn more","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_DONATE_NOW":"Donate now","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_FACT":"Quick fact:","LOC_HOMEPAGE_GALLERY_CARD_TITLE":"Recent Homepage images","LOC_HOMEPAGE_VERTICAL_SCROLL_GALLERY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"Homepage image for {0}","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_TITLE":"On this day in history","LOC_HOMEPAGE_ON_THIS_DAY_IMAGE_ARIALABEL":"On this day in {0}, {1}","LOC_H